  "generatedAt": "2026-06-15T13:10:59.837Z",
  "summary": "## Cursor Agents Toolkit\n\nArcade toolkit for operating [Cursor Cloud Agents](https://cursor.com) — launch AI coding agents on GitHub repositories, manage their lifecycle, and inspect results programmatically.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n- **Agent lifecycle management** — launch agents against repos or named environments, archive/unarchive reversibly, or permanently delete them.\n- **Run control & polling** — start runs, send follow-up prompts (one active run at a time), cancel in-flight runs, and poll status until terminal; handles async cancellation and `[agent_busy]` / `[run_not_cancellable]` error codes.\n- **Result & output inspection** — retrieve completed run status, result text, branches, and PRs; list all runs for an agent (newest first); download time-limited links for explicitly uploaded artifacts.\n- **Account & resource discovery** — verify the authenticated account (`WhoAmI`), enumerate accessible GitHub repositories, list available LLM models (Claude, GPT, Gemini families) for launch configuration.\n- **Usage & observability** — fetch per-agent token usage summarized across all runs and broken down per run.\n\n## Secrets\n\n`CURSOR_AGENTS_API_KEY` — A Cursor API key that authenticates all calls to the Cursor Cloud Agents API. To obtain one, log into your [Cursor account dashboard](https://cursor.com), navigate to **Settings → API Keys** (or the equivalent account/developer section), and generate a new key. The key must belong to an account that has Cursor Cloud Agent access enabled; free-tier accounts may not have this feature. Store the generated key immediately — Cursor typically does not show it again after creation. Call `CursorAgents.WhoAmI` after configuring the secret to confirm the key resolves to the expected account before launching any agents.\n\nFor instructions on adding secrets to your Arcade environment, see the [Arcade secrets guide](https://docs.arcade.dev/en/guides/create-tools/tool-basics/create-tool-secrets). You can manage secrets directly at [https://api.arcade.dev/dashboard/auth/secrets](https://api.arcade.dev/dashboard/auth/secrets)."
}